# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1885-baltimore-orioles-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] The 19th century's version of the **Baltimore Orioles** were founded in 1882 as part of the new American Association.
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] Owned by wealthy Harry Von der Horst, the Orioles finished the season in last place with only 19 wins.
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1885-boston-beaneaters-season] The **1885 Boston Beaneaters season** was the 15th season of the franchise.
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1885-boston-beaneaters-season] The team finished in fifth place in the National League with a record of 46–66, 41 games behind the Chicago White Stockings.
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1885-brooklyn-grays-season] The **1885 Brooklyn Grays** finished the season in fifth place.
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1885-brooklyn-grays-season] The team added several players from the defunct Cleveland Blues team after team owner Charlie Byrne bought the Blues assets for $10,000 after the 1884 season.
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1885-buffalo-bisons-season] The **1885 Buffalo Bisons** finished the season with a 38–74 record, good for seventh place in the National League.
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1885-buffalo-bisons-season] As things continued to implode on the field, the team ownership sold the whole franchise to the Detroit Wolverines.
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1885-buffalo-bisons-season] With all their players gone, the team finished out the season with local amateurs filling in.
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1885-chicago-white-stockings-season] The **1885 Chicago White Stockings season** was the 14th season of the Chicago White Stockings franchise, the tenth in the National League and the first at the first West Side Park.
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1885-chicago-white-stockings-season] The White Stockings won the National League pennant for the first time since 1882, beating the New York Giants by two games.
[src:1885-baltimore-orioles-season/1885-chicago-white-stockings-season] The series ended without a champion, with both teams winning three games with one tie.
